# PDF Clickable Links

When markdown is rendered to PDF (xhtml2pdf, pandoc, md-to-pdf), link syntax in source must produce **visible plain text** with working hyperlinks — never raw `[label](url)` in the PDF output.

## Markdown source rules

| Element | Source format | Why |
|---------|---------------|-----|
| Email | `jozanini@example.com` (plain) | Converter auto-wraps as `mailto:` |
| Phone | `(555) 010-0200` (plain) | Converter auto-wraps as `tel:` |
| Labeled link | `[LinkedIn](https://...)` | Label shows; URL is hidden |
| Bare URL in body | `https://...` or `[label](url)` | Auto-link or explicit markdown |

**Never** put `[email](mailto:email@domain.com)` in markdown source when a post-processing autolink step runs — it double-wraps and the PDF shows literal bracket syntax.

## Converter requirements

If adding or changing `autolink` / pre-PDF processing:

1. **Protect** existing `[text](url)` markdown links before regex passes.
2. Auto-link bare emails, phones, and URLs only where not already linked.
3. CSS must style anchors: `a { color: #0563c1; text-decoration: underline; }`

## Verification

After PDF generation, confirm in output (not just markdown):

- Email displays as `user@domain.com`, clickable
- Phone displays as `(xxx) xxx-xxxx`, clickable
- LinkedIn shows word "LinkedIn", not a raw URL
- No visible `](mailto:` or `](tel:` artifacts

